This paper deals with efficient feature selection for supervised sequence labeling using conditional random fields (CRFs). The paper discusses the use of an l1 penalty to impose sparsity on the parameter set, which is a common technique in machine learning for feature selection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of CRFs for image labeling, which suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and pattern recognition (cs.CR).
